This collection documents the life and activities of Sylvia Beach (1887-1962),
                   the American author, publisher, and owner of Shakespeare & Company, the
                   Paris bookshop that was a meeting-point for French, English, Irish and American
                   writers during the 1920's and 1930's. The collection consists largely of files
                   relating to Shakespeare & Company; Beach's writings and translations, in
                   particular her memoir Shakespeare & Company ;
                   and files relating to the circle of artists and writers surrounding her
                   throughout her life. Included are family, personal, and business correspondence;
                   business records of Shakespeare & Company; personal and family records;
                   manuscripts and artwork by members of her circle; photographs; and memorabilia.
